@startuml
!include /Users/Q284340/Agentic/coding/docs/puml/_standard-style.puml

title Agent Persistent Memory Files — Read/Write Lifecycle

participant "Claude Agent" as Agent
participant "MEMORY.md\n(Index)" as Index
participant "memory/*.md\n(Topic Files)" as TopicFiles
participant "Auto-Memory\nSystem" as AutoMem
participant "Conversation\nContext" as Context

== Session Start: Memory Load ==

Agent -> Index : read MEMORY.md (index)
Index --> Agent : list of topic file pointers
Agent -> TopicFiles : read relevant topic files
TopicFiles --> Agent : user prefs, feedback, project state
Agent -> Context : inject memory into working context

== During Session: Knowledge Acquisition ==

Agent -> Agent : detect new user preference\nor feedback signal
Agent -> AutoMem : classify memory type\n(user / feedback / project / reference)

alt New memory
    AutoMem -> TopicFiles : write <topic>.md\nwith frontmatter + body
    AutoMem -> Index : append one-line pointer to MEMORY.md
else Update existing
    AutoMem -> TopicFiles : surgical replace in existing file
    note right : keep Why: and How to apply: lines\nup to date
end

== Recall: Stale Memory Check ==

Agent -> TopicFiles : read memory referencing\na file path or function name
TopicFiles --> Agent : stored claim (may be stale)
Agent -> Agent : verify claim against current\ncodebase state

alt Still valid
    Agent -> Context : apply memory as context
else Stale / contradicted
    Agent -> TopicFiles : update or remove stale entry
    Agent -> Index : update pointer if filename changed
    Agent -> Context : apply observed current state
end

== Fault: MEMORY.md Overflow ==

AutoMem -> Index : attempt append
Index --> AutoMem : WARNING — line count > 200\n(truncation risk)
AutoMem -> Index : trim verbose entries\nshorten to ≤150 chars/line
AutoMem -> TopicFiles : move detail into topic file\n(not the index)

== Session End ==

Agent -> Context : discard ephemeral task state
note over TopicFiles : persisted memories survive\ninto future conversations

@enduml